                  <p class="subtitle">
                    Fitrana, also known as Zakat-ul-Fitr, is a form of charity given at the end of Ramadan or the day of Eid-Ul-Fitr before the Salah. It is an essential Islamic practice aimed at purifying the fast and ensuring that everyone can partake in the joy of Eid. Unlike Zakat, which is calculated on annual savings, Fitrana is a fixed amount given per person in a household. It is typically provided in the form of food or its monetary equivalent.

                  </p>
