                  <div class="donation-content">
                    <h4 class="title">Zakat ul Fitr: A Spiritual Responsibility
                    </h4>
                    <p class="pera">
                        Zakat ul Fitr holds immense spiritual significance. It serves as a means of purification, compensating for any shortcomings in fasting during Ramadan. Paying Fitrana is obligatory for every Muslim who possesses enough food to last for the day. The head of the household is responsible for paying it on behalf of all dependents, including children and elders.

                    </p>
                    <ul class="bullet-list">
                        <li class="list">
                          <span style="font-weight: 700;">Spiritual Significance:</span>
                           Zakat ul Fitr is a vital act of worship, symbolizing purification and compensating for any imperfections in fasting during Ramadan.

                        </li>
                        <li class="list">
                          <span style="font-weight: 700;">Obligatory for Muslims:</span>
                          It is a mandatory duty for every Muslim who has sufficient food for a day.

                        </li>
                        <li class="list">
                          <span style="font-weight: 700;">Household Responsibility:</span>
                           The head of the family is accountable for paying Zakat ul Fitr on behalf of all dependents, including children and elders.

                        </li>
